=== test.181: brcmf_chip_set_active (ARM release) isolation — stage=0 ===
Date: Mon 20 Apr 18:52:02 BST 2026

Stage 0: skip_arm=1 — download_fw_nvram: enter_download_state (read-only) + BAR2 ioread32 probe + 442KB iowrite32 fw; sleeps 100 ms, reads host resetintr from fw->data, writes NVRAM to BAR2, reads the ramsize-4 NVRAM marker, reads TCM[0x0..0x1c], attempts INTERNAL_MEM resetcore (expected NULL on BCM4360), then probe CR4 + brcmf_chip_set_active(ci, resetintr) + probe CR4 at 20 ms + probe CR4 at 100 ms. BusMaster remains cleared. Releases fw/NVRAM, returns -ENODEV.
(test.181: test.180 showed INTERNAL_MEM core is absent on BCM4360. This run adds brcmf_chip_set_active(ci, resetintr) — the ARM release — with pre/post CR4 probes. BusMaster stays cleared so firmware cannot DMA to host during the observation window. Returns -ENODEV before any sharedram polling or normal attach.)

=== Pre-test BAR0 MMIO guard ===
BAR0 MMIO UR/I/O error (6ms) — device alive; SBR in probe should fix. Proceeding.

